# HMS Backend Implementation Plan

## Overview

Implement a complete Django + MongoEngine backend for the Hospital Management System and wire it to the existing Next.js frontend. The system uses two MongoDB databases (`hms_archive` for permanent records, `hms_active` for in-progress sessions) and serves 35 API endpoints across 5 role-based modules.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **MongoDB Atlas**: This implementation requires a MongoDB Atlas cluster (or local MongoDB replica set) since transactions span two databases. You'll need to provide connection URIs in `.env`. Do you already have Atlas clusters set up, or should I provide guidance on that?

> [!WARNING]
> **Frontend role naming mismatch**: The frontend uses `counsellor` and `pharmacist` as role names, while the architecture plan uses `consultant` and `pharmacy`. The backend API paths use `/consultant/` and `/pharmacy/` per the architecture plan. The frontend integration layer will map between these naming conventions without changing any UI code.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Invoice screens**: The frontend has invoice screens (`/pharmacy/invoices`, invoice generation in dispense page). Since invoice generation is explicitly out of scope per the architecture plan, these frontend screens will continue to use demo data. The dispense endpoint will handle stock deduction and visit archiving but not invoice creation.

