### Component 9: Sessions App & Archive Service

Session lifecycle and atomic archive operation.

---

#### [NEW] [apps/sessions/views.py](file:///home/bastard/Desktop/b_hB1FLZHsGiY-1774459584029/hms_backend/apps/sessions/views.py)
Shared session utility views if needed (most session operations handled in role-specific apps).

#### [NEW] [apps/sessions/archive_service.py](file:///home/bastard/Desktop/b_hB1FLZHsGiY-1774459584029/hms_backend/apps/sessions/archive_service.py)
Atomic transaction service:
1. Read active session with all stage data
2. Construct `Visit` document from session data
3. In a MongoDB transaction: insert `Visit` → push `visit_id` onto `Patient.visit_ids` + increment `visit_count` + set `last_visit_at` → delete `ActiveSession` → delete `ActiveLock`
4. Return serialized archived visit
5. Full rollback on any failure

